            "body": "9.2.0350 is relevant for auto-patching the applicable test files.\r\nI understand that many test files/scripts are behind or not fully compatible (due to Vim9 refactor) so it's simpler to mark it `modelinestrict` N/A now.\r\nBut, that won't mark the followup patches that will amend the option whitelist as N/A.\r\n\r\nInstead, update dev_vimpatch.txt and relevant files/scripts to state `modelinestrict` option is N/A and link to the security issues.",
